On the newest episode of YippieYay!, Yappy & Yoli meet a clown & get to play with puppets! 🤡 🎉 
Getting to work with & incorporate a puppet on this episode was such a dream for me! It funny enough all started with my love for @AvenueQMusical! But seeing how much joy @SesameStreet, @HensonCompany, & @TheMuppets have given to kids all over the world has always inspired me so much as an actor.

So to finally be able to do it on my own kid's show was priceless & definitely made my love for puppets only get stronger! There's so many incredible ways to entertain, educate, & spark kid's imaginations! I can't wait to incorporate puppetry into my repertoire even more now! 🥺💕

Hey Tennessee lawmakers, your disgusting new laws against drag queens, the trans community, & queer artists doesn't protect kids. It just further spreads hate against an already marginalized community. You're over sexualizing & using our community as scapegoats when there are a billion other actual problems in the world that's actually harming everyone, such as gun violence, climate disasters, corrupt politicians, & sexually abusive religious figures. 

Do the kids in this video look like they're in danger? I'm in drag as Winifred Sanderson, along with my cis female Sarah & Mary performers, and all I see are kids jumping around, innocently having a fun time experiencing the magic of Hocus Pocus in person with their families! 

Should kids be at every drag performance? No! Of course not. Some are adult in nature, which is no different than using discretion to not take kids to straight strip clubs, cabaret shows, & other types of adult shows. It should be up to the parents to regulate where they take their kids! But you are specifically targeting a primarily queer art form because you are homophobic. What a lot of us do is no different than the characters you'd see at a theme park or on a kid's TV show. I can guarantee you drag queens have never harmed any kids. You will not silence us.

Well, I just got out of seeing @DisneyLittleMermaid with my family! 🥹😭😍 I've waited for this movie for SO damn long. I've dreamt of a live action Little Mermaid since I was a kid. Some may not know this, but this was always my absolute favorite animated Disney film. And boy....this didn't disappoint!

I CRIED. SO MUCH!!! I had chills the entire time. THIS is how you do a live action remake! The best one yet! First off, @HalleBailey as Ariel is sheer perfection. What more can I say? I had chills the entire time she was on screen. That girl is a star. She IS Ariel. Probably some of the most brilliant casting I've ever seen. She's a living angel. 

Now, @MelissaMcCarthy...pretty damn fabulous as Ursula! She had SO much fun with this role!!! While I obviously am a bit biased & would have preferred a talented singing drag queen (*cough* @GingerMinj *cough*), I still loved her as Ursula! That makeup was...a choice though lol. Overall, I was very happy with Melissa as Ursula! She did the role justice!

The rest of the cast was fabulous as well! All in all, it was such a gorgeous tribute to the original, while also being able to stand on its own with enough great changes! I wasn't nuts about a lot of the CGI, I'll echo what most have said that some of it felt a little uncanny valley & wonky/video game-y at times. It was gorgeous in 3D as well! But some of the new changes/songs I wasn't a fan of tbh. Scuttle's song in particular took me completely out of the movie & I did not like it. But omg I screamed when a certain big cameo happened. 

All that being said, it was stunning. And I cried. A lot. And I will be seeing it in theatres SO many times!!! Bravo, Disney!

I'm SO happy I got to share my first time with my mom & sister, and THAT was so priceless. And thank you to @AMCTheatres for the poster! 🥹😭🧜🏽‍♀️💜 🦑 🐚 🎶
